Section 1:
SR 26 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 26 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 26(By Senators Weld, Smith (Mr. President), Jeffries, and Rucker)[Introduced March 12, 2025] Recognizing March 13, 2025, as National K9 Veterans Day at the Legislature.Whereas, Since 1942, with the inception of the War Dog Program on March 13, the United States K9 Corps has been recognized for their outstanding contributions; andWhereas, Initiated by Joe White, a Vietnam veteran and K9 handler, K9 Veterans Day was established to observe the service and sacrifice of the United States military working dogs and has been set aside annually to honor and acknowledge these courageous dogs since WWII; andWhereas, It has long been known that dogs are man’s best friend, but more importantly, along with the depth of integrity combined with their innate sense to protect, and their intelligence to learn, has made these K9 veterans an invaluable asset; andWhereas, K9 troops also provide another service when on the battlefield in that they are a sense of comfort to a war-worn troop, forming an unbreakable bond with their handler; andWhereas, To further enhance the K9 veterans they are traditionally ranked higher than their handlers ensuring the respect and importance these K9s bring to the battlefield; andWhereas, The K9 Corps first recruited civilian dogs and their owners and trained them for various duties, such as scout, sentry, and messenger roles.  Over the years these responsibilities have grown to include search and rescue, critical roles in patrol, and detection in drug and bomb operations; andWhereas, This day is not just for military dogs, but to also recognize the many services our K9s provide to police, fire, and search and rescue teams; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate recognizes March 13, 2025, as K9 Veterans Day at the Legislature; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the appropriate representative of the War Dog Guardians. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


